<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="326" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1773,2014]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="326" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1845,1870]" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Remarks.</emphasis>
The two specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[608,690,1845,1870]" name="Taiwan" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
have a tegmental sculpture very similar to that of specimens from the 
<collectingCountry box="[194,383,1881,1906]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 1998" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[540,996,1881,1906]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis box="[540,828,1881,1906]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Leptochiton vietnamensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko" box="[837,996,1881,1906]" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" refId="ref16940" refString="Sirenko, V. I. (1998) One more deep water chiton Leptoсhiton vietnamensis sp. n. (Мollusca, Polyplacophora) living and feeding on sunken wood from the South China Sea. Rutheniсa, 8, 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1998">Sirenko, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko" box="[1012,1183,1881,1906]" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" refId="ref17401" refString="Sirenko, V. I. (2016 b) New and rare species of the genus Lepidozona (Мollusca: Polyplacophora) from the South China, East China and Philippine seas. The Bulletin of the Russian Far East Malaсologiсal soсiety, 20 (2), 28 - 46." type="journal article" year="2016" yearSuffix="a">Sirenko 2016a</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens from the 
<collectingCountry box="[195,385,1917,1942]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[446,528,1917,1942]" name="Taiwan" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[702,873,1918,1941]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis box="[702,873,1918,1941]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">L vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by their numerous aesthetes in each granule, by having protruding aesthete caps, in radula morphology and in having spicules on the girdle, but differ by the sculpture of the tegmentum. Raised granules are arranged in distinct longitudinal rows with interstices on the central area of intermediate valves and on the antemucronal area of the tail valve in 
<emphasis box="[1102,1284,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[1102,1280,153,176]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">L. vietnamensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, on the same areas of specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[546,734,188,213]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
and from 
<collectingCountry box="[855,940,188,213]" name="Taiwan" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, longitudinal rows of flattened granules are hardly visible and evident only near the apex, but other surfaces of the central and postmucronal areas have granules arranged in a random manner. In order to clear up the taxonomical status of the specimens it is necessary to carry out additional examinations of all species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[786,961,297,320]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis box="[786,961,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">L. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nierstrasz, 1905)" authorityName="Nierstrasz" authorityYear="1905" baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1088,1388,295,320]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rissoi">
<emphasis box="[1088,1103,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1117,1179,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">rissoi</emphasis>
(Nierstrasz, 1905)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,285,332,357]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,285,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. from the 
<collectingCountry box="[433,624,332,357]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
